[SN]TITLE[SN]
Graeme Wood: 'The rise of IS is the modern Reformation'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Viewsnight is BBC Newsnight's new place for ideas and opinion.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
16 February 2017 Last updated at 10:01 GMT
Here, Graeme Wood, national correspondent for The Atlantic argues the rise of so-called Islamic State is a kind of Reformation within Islam.
We also hear from Tariq Ramadan who says this argument is "misplaced" and we should not try to "understand Islam through a Christian lens".
